FBIS4-63773 "drsov101_e_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Zlenko Seeks International `Response' to Crimean Issue Zlenko Seeks International `Response' to Crimean Issue WS2505080994 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1800 GMT 24 May 94 WS2505080994 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Ukrainian BFN [Text] Speaking to reporters after talks with British Foreign Minister Hurd, Ukrainian Foreign Minister Zlenko stressed that the Crimean legislature's decision to introduce changes to the Ukrainian Constitution is in violation of the constitution. Zlenko added: We would like to draw the international community's attention to this issue, and we would like to hear this community's response regarding our domestic problems -- Ukraine's territorial integrity, sovereignty, and independence.
